    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <head>No. 119.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dichman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Colon, Aspinwall, United States of Colombia</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 14, 1878</date>. (Received August
                        23.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In order to furnish the Department as speedily as
                    possible with the information requested in the Department’s dispatch No. 4 of
                    the 26th ultimo, which I received before leaving the United States, I herewith
                    forward a copy of the Official Gazette (Diario Oficial), containing the law of
                    the Colombian Congress approving of the convention concluded between the United
                    States of Colombia and the International Interoceanic Canal Company, and the
                    decrees issued in accordance therewith. The paper and translation have been
                    kindly furnished to me by Mr. B. Mozley, the general superintendent of the
                    Panama Railroad Company, and the Pacific Mail Steamship Company.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>Very, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ERNEST DICHMAN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
